6. Research simple fixes or mitigations for found vulnerabilities

1)Disable weak ciphers like TLS_RSA_WITH_SEED_CBC_SHA in PostgreSQL SSL/TLS config.

2)Restrict TLS versions to TLS 1.2+ (preferably TLS 1.3 if supported).

3)Update PostgreSQL and OpenSSL to the latest stable version.

4)Use strong cipher suites, e.g., TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384.

5)Apply recommended configs from Mozilla SSL Config Generator.

6)Configure postgresql.conf with ssl_ciphers option to whitelist strong ciphers only.

7)Ensure 2048+ bit RSA keys or ECC keys are used for certificates.

8)Regularly scan with tools like OpenVAS, Qualys, or SSL Labs.

9)Use Letâ€™s Encrypt or another CA for modern, secure certs instead of self-signed with weak params.

10)Apply security baselines from NIST, BSI, or ENISA TLS guidelines.
